text: Shirley Wilmotte Wynne M.D., Dr. P.H. (1882-1942) was the New York City Health Commissioner from 1928 through 1933. He was considered “a leader in public health and child welfare initiatives throughout his career.”, ==References== Category:Commissioners of Health of the City of New York Category:1882 births Category:1942 deaths
title: Shirley W. Wynne
